node.text:
When a city becomes your boulder 🧗 

📽 @oliver_thorpe
📍 Aarhus, Denmark

Bouldering is a form of free climbing that is performed on small rock formations or artificial rock walls without the use of ropes or harnesses. While bouldering can be done without any equipment, most climbers use climbing shoes to help secure footholds, chalk to keep their hands dry and to provide a firmer grip, and bouldering mats to prevent injuries from falls. Unlike free solo climbing, which is also performed without ropes, bouldering problems (the sequence of moves that a climber performs to complete the climb) are usually less than 6 meters (20 ft.) tall.

node.text:
This Google Earth street view via @hidden.on.google.earth form part of an outdoor exhibition, named Goldwell Open Air Museum, it can be found just off the road leading to the famous Death Valley desert. A collection of statues created by Belgian artist Albert Szukalski.

The group of life-sized sculptures dressed in white were installed in the town in 1984 as a “modern day representation of Christ’s Last Supper”, according to the museum’s website.

Szukalski followed up the imposing piece the same year with a smaller feature – ‘Ghost Rider’ – which is non other than the bicycle man highlighted by Cline in his clip.

📽 @hidden.on.google.earth #nature
📍Death Valley National Park, Nevada
